  "prompt": "How do I write a good essay for the SAT?",
  "response": "Here are some key tips for writing a strong SAT essay:\n\n1. Understand the prompt\n- Read it carefully\n- Identify the main argument and key points\n\n2. Take a clear position\n- Develop a strong thesis statement\n- Choose a side and stick to it throughout the essay\n\n3. Structure your essay\n- Introduction: Thesis statement\n- Body paragraphs: 2-3 examples supporting your argument\n- Conclusion: Restate thesis and summarize main points\n\n4. Use evidence\n- Include specific examples from literature, history, current events\n- Cite concrete details to support your argument\n- Demonstrate critical thinking\n\n5. Write clearly and coherently\n- Use varied sentence structure\n- Write legibly\n- Stay focused and organized\n- Demonstrate strong vocabulary\n\n6. Analyze the source text\n- Break down the author's argument\n- Explain how they use rhetorical strategies\n- Show persuasive techniques\n\n7. Manage your time\n- Spend ~2-3 minutes planning\n- ~20 minutes writing\n- ~2-3 minutes proofreading\n\n8. Practice\n- Take practice tests\n- Time yourself\n- Review and learn from mistakes\n\nRemember: Strong writing, clear reasoning, and effective use of evidence are key.",
